# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MachineVerse — environment template
#
# Copy this file to `.env` (it's gitignored) and fill in the keys you have.
# You only need ONE provider configured for the app to work — the gateway
# falls through the list in lib/llm/config.ts until something succeeds.
#
# Recommended minimum: at least one Gemini key (best free quality + web
# grounding) plus Groq (huge free quota, very fast). Both are free.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── Gemini ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Round-robin pool. The gateway picks the next available key per request
# and cools any key down for 60s after a 429 / RESOURCE_EXHAUSTED error.
# You can leave gaps — the gateway only uses what's set.
#
# Get free keys at: https://aistudio.google.com/app/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY_1=
GEMINI_API_KEY_2=
GEMINI_API_KEY_3=
GEMINI_API_KEY_4=
GEMINI_API_KEY_5=

# Legacy single-key slot — still honored if the _1..5 slots are empty.
GEMINI_API_KEY=

# ── Groq ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Llama 3.3 70B on free tier. Very fast (~300 tokens/sec), generous quota.
# Get a key at: https://console.groq.com/keys
GROQ_API_KEY=

# ── OpenRouter ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# We use the DeepSeek free tier (deepseek-chat-v3.1:free).
# Get a key at: https://openrouter.ai/keys
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=

# ── Cerebras ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Free tier on Cerebras's hosted inference (Llama 4 Scout).
# Sign up + grab a key at: https://cloud.cerebras.ai/
CEREBRAS_API_KEY=

# ── GitHub Models ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Free for any GitHub account (preview). Reuses your GitHub PAT —
# any classic or fine-grained token with `read:user` scope works.
# Tokens: https://github.com/settings/tokens
# Catalog: https://github.com/marketplace/models
GITHUB_TOKEN=

# ── Mistral (optional, currently unused) ───────────────────────────────
# Reserved for future addition to the provider chain. La Plateforme
# has a small free tier: https://console.mistral.ai/api-keys/
MISTRAL_API_KEY=

# ── Web search (for grounding non-Gemini providers) ────────────────────
# When a non-Gemini provider answers a chat query, the gateway runs an
# external web search and injects the top snippets into the system prompt.
# This makes answers fresh and citable even when Gemini fails.
#
# Backend priority:
#   1. TAVILY_API_KEY set    → Tavily (best quality, 1000 free queries/mo)
#                              https://app.tavily.com/
#   2. SERPAPI_API_KEY set   → SerpAPI (100 free queries/mo)
#                              https://serpapi.com/manage-api-key
#   3. nothing set           → DuckDuckGo HTML scrape (no key, unlimited,
#                              less polished but works 24/7)
#
# Recommended: leave both empty until you see DDG returning poor results.
TAVILY_API_KEY=
SERPAPI_API_KEY=

# ── Ollama (local fallback) ────────────────────────────────────────────
# No key needed. Install Ollama (https://ollama.com/download) and run:
#   ollama pull llama3.2:3b
#   ollama pull qwen2.5:7b
# The gateway probes http://localhost:11434 at startup; if reachable,
# it's used as the final fallback when every cloud provider fails.
OLLAMA_BASE_URL=http://localhost:11434/v1

# ── Gateway tuning ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Set LLM_LOG=off to silence the per-request `[llm] TRY/OK/FAIL` lines.
LLM_LOG=

# ── Auth (Google sign-in) ──────────────────────────────────────────────
# Required for /api/auth/* and any feature that gates on `auth()` —
# saved chat history (/api/chats) and per-user persistence in the
# streaming chat route.
#
# 1. Generate AUTH_SECRET:  openssl rand -base64 32
# 2. Create an OAuth client at https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#    Application type: Web. Authorized redirect URIs:
#      http://localhost:3000/api/auth/callback/google
#      https://<your-vercel-domain>/api/auth/callback/google
# 3. Drop the client id / secret here, plus on Vercel.
AUTH_SECRET=
AUTH_GOOGLE_ID=
AUTH_GOOGLE_SECRET=

# Only set this if your deploy sits behind a proxy that doesn't forward
# the host header correctly. Vercel sets this automatically — leave blank.
# NEXTAUTH_URL=

# ── Chat history storage (Upstash Redis) ───────────────────────────────
# If both vars are set, per-user chat threads are stored in Upstash.
# If either is missing, the app falls back to a local JSON file at
# .data/chats.json (fine for `next dev`, NOT for Vercel — serverless
# filesystems are ephemeral).
#
# Free tier: https://console.upstash.com/redis → Create database →
# select "REST" → copy URL + Token.
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_URL=
UPSTASH_REDIS_REST_TOKEN=
